The paper deals with constructing spanners in geometric intersection graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of partitioning and bichromatic closest pair problems suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The mention of diameter approximation and geometric graph separators suggests that the paper may also be relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT).
